f5d20.textContent:
LTB4 would normally bind to its receptor LTB4R and 
consequently activate AKT1 and NFkB pathway.
However, when RvE1 is present, it binds to the receptoor,
 therefore inhibitimng the binding of LTB4 and inhibiting 
the NFkB pathway as well.

f9cc0.textContent:
RvE2 also has a very similar function as RvE1, 
however the latter was found to be a stronger 
activator of the receptor CMKLR1.
